+section("Colors")
  p Colors are divided into <strong>Primary, Tints</strong> and <strong>Shades</strong>. All colors are available as sass variables in the <code>/src/sass/base/color.scss</code>file. The primary colors are: <code>$blue</code>, <code>$navy</code>, <code>$anchor</code>, <code>$purple</code>, <code>$black</code>, <code>$violet</code>, <code>$electric</code> and <code>$white</code>.

  p Colors can also be accessed using special helper classes in HTML: For example, <code class="c-blue">.c-blue</code> to change the colour to blue and <code class="bg-blue c-white">.bg-blue</code> to change the background to blue.
